Oh and P.S.  Do NOT fill it with tap water or use tap water for  top-off.  You will regret it very badly.  Either get a water filter and mix your own saltwater or buy water from your LFS...tap water=VERY BAD <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=199808"><img src="http://www.forthworld.net/fridge/vitasanstfu.jpg"><br> <br><SELECT NAME="FORM_Characters"> <OPTION SELECTED value="Sanndor Draggonforge 65 Dwarven Overlord"> Sanndor Draggonforge 65 Dwarven Overlord <OPTION Value="Hotto 55 Halfing Druid" > Hotto 55 Halfling Druid <OPTION Value="Mikken 42 Wood Elf Ranger" > Mikken 42 Wood Elf Ranger <OPTION Value="Zanndor 42 Barb Rogue" > Zanndor 42 Barb Rogue <OPTION Value="Greywen 40 Gnome Mage" > Greywen 40 Gnome Mage <OPTION Value="Merryn Danome 32 Gnome Necro" > Merryn Danome 32 Gnome Necro  <br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub134.ezboard.com/btabularasa19500.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merryndanome>Merryn Danome</A> at: 1/13/04 4:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub134.ezboard.com/btabularasa19500.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skarphace>SkarPhace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table style='Filter: Glow(Color=#9999FF,strength=2)'><tr><td><span class='usertitle'><font color=#000000><b>I'm a Posting Whore!!</span></font></td></tr></TABLE></b></span><br>  Posts: 480<br> <font color=#9999FF>(1/14/04 8:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p197.ezboard.com/ftabularasa19500frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3142.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Freshwater Aquarium or Saltwater</span><hr size=1>     Man seeing all this puts me in the mood to have fish again.  Glad to see salt has gotten easier but the expense is still a bit more than I would want.  salt is very pretty with the very different types of fish you can put in there but they are very sensitive to changes in PH and if you have any problems fish start dieing and it get both frustrating and expensive.  Like has been said fresh water is easier because in my view the fish are much less fragile.  Ballz list is a good one for interesting fresh water fish.  I always enjoyed convicts, and an assortment of cichlids.  Of course some folks would  say dont mix south American cichlids with Africans but I've seen it done.  Africans are very agressive.  <br>
    When I was in college I had 2 roomates in 3 bedroom apt and we had 3 tanks in the living room a 55gal long, 45 gal tall and a 65 gal breeder tank which was our salt tank.  The other two were fresh water.  Then we each had a 20 gal in our bedrooms.   Living Rock whats that hehe we had under gravel filtration and power heads with a debris filter on these.  We did have to clean our tanks periodically and the salt one was an absolute pain in the ass.  But from what I'm reading above all the waiting for the water to culture and adding one fish in at a time is a thing of the past.<br>
