<br>
First, thanks all for the support and feedback.  I didn't go for Salt water.  (Due to money issues and I want to re learn how to take care of fish again)  My 30 gallon tank is doing well soo far.  I ran the tank one week before adding any fish.  I have 2 Gold Gourami, 1 Dwarf Gourami and 2 Ornate Cory Cat fish.  <br>
<br>
I like the Gourami's soo far.  Both the Gold and Dwarf are doing very well so far.  I plan on getting some more Gourami's after the first month is over. (Cycling) Also, I will get two more Cory Cat's (they do well keeping the bottom clean)  <br>
<br>
Tetra's will be the next fish I get.  Some Bleeding Hearts (childhood favorite), Rummynose Tetra and some German Blue Ram fish. (Not Tetra's)  Also, the a school of Lemon or Neon Tetra's.  I'm not sure yet.  <br>
<br>
I will have Angelfish also.  I bought them young (about a quarter in size) I know they can be Semi-aggressive, but I had 4 when I was a kid.  They did very well back then.  I'm not sure if I will get 4 this time tho.  My mother has 2 Angelfish now in her 20 Gallon tank.  Once in a while our blusher chases the Golden Angelfish, but they are doing great for the most part.  They have been together for over one month now.  (When they out grow the tank, I will return them back)<br>
<br>
If you guys have any idea's of fish I can buy, please post. :) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170064"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://img6.photobucket.com/albums/v19/Foolio/Sigs/melficesig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub134.ezboard.com/btabularasa19500.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sticklial>Sticklial</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table style='filter: glow(color=white,strength=3)'><tr><td><span class='usertitle'><font face=tahoma color=green><b>Odds are, he's LD right now</b></font></span></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 2414<br> <font color=#9999FF>(2/9/04 3:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p197.ezboard.com/ftabularasa19500frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3142.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Freshwater Aquarium or Saltwater</span><hr size=1> <br>
